column28:
{"submitted": "2025-05-13T08:38:57.127-05:00", "type": "vendor_self", "region": "North America", "updated": "2025-05-13T08:38:57.166-05:00", "url": "https://www.g2.com/products/sage-intacct/reviews/11160467", "title": "Great experience with the software", "primary": "Americas", "switched_from": {"products": [{"id": "4111", "name": "QuickBooks Desktop Enterprise", "slug": "quickbooks-desktop-enterprise"}], "reason": "We switched from QuickBooks Desktop because it lacked the scalability and advanced features we needed as our organization grew. Managing multiple users, entities, and more complex workflows became increasingly difficult. QuickBooks also had limited automation and reporting capabilities, which made tasks like invoice tracking and approvals more manual and time-consuming.
Sage Intacct offers a significant upgrade in terms of functionality, automation, and visibility. The cloud-based platform allows multiple users to access the system securely from anywhere, which QuickBooks Desktop didn’t support. Intacct also provides stronger internal controls, audit trails, and customizable reporting, which are essential for more robust financial management.

In terms of accounts payable and receivable, Intacct is more streamlined and easier to scale, with better integration options like Hybrent, and a more organized way of handling invoice workflows. While it does take some time to learn, the efficiency and accuracy improvements have made the transition worthwhile"}}

